### Die {#acbaa4a80bd8f05f262dcffa77f30796f}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::atomic&lt;DIE &#42;&gt; llvm::dwarf&#95;linker::parallel::TypeEntryBody::Die = &#123;nullptr&#125;</>}>
<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarf-linker/parallel/typeentrybody">TypeEntryBody</a> keeps partially cloned DIEs corresponding to this type.

The two kinds of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> can be kept: declaration and definition. If definition <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> was met while parsing input DWARF then this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> would be used as a final <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> for this type. If definition <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> is not met then declaration <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> would be used as a final <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a>.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/dwarflinker/lib/dwarflinker/parallel/typepool-h/#l00059">59</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/dwarflinker/lib/dwarflinker/parallel/typepool-h">TypePool.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
